    <h2>about top 3 central universities</h2>
     
                       
 




         <h5>2. Banaras Hindu University (BHU) </h5>
         Founded in 1916, the Shri Pandit Madan Mohan Malviya Banaras Hindu University has become a university of national importance. 
         The huge varsity of 140 departments, 14 faculties, women’s college, and interdisciplinary centres,
         has made this university one of the esteemed Universities and has ranked at the top of every student’s wishlist.
         This university has been recognized by UGC and has ranked in the 3rd position in the NIRF rank list. <br> <br> <br> <br>


         <div class="jnu">
         
                       <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Banaras_Hindu_University">

                    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/ca/Banaras_Hindu_University_Emblem_Seal_Transparent.png/150px-Banaras_Hindu_University_Emblem_Seal_Transparent.png" alt="" class="jnu">


                       </a>
         </div>





          <h5>3. Jamia MiJamia Millia Islamia </h5>
            University is situated in the heart of Delhi. Established in 1920, 
             this university has extended itself to a huge extent. 9 faculties, 38 departments, and 27 learning and research centres,
             have made NAAC offer it grade A++. This UGC-recognized university has secured 6th position in the university category,
             and 13th position in the overall category in the NIRF rank list, 2021. <br> <br> <br> <br>

